			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What do we want for AA's?  Keep in mind the next expansion (purely speculating here) will probably add a good 400 or 500 AA's to keep the powergamers happy, with a lot of the "icing" abilities, such as earth form, at very large prices.
<br />

<br />
We already know that there will be elemental forms level 4 and 5, or at least, there's a DAMN good chance we'll get these in the new expansion.
<br />

<br />
Here is what I would like to see:
<br />

<br />
<ul>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Advanced Spell Casting Mastery: </span> Doesn't have to add much, but just enough to give a nice edge, make it another 1, 2, and 3 % pres, that would be enough to make it worthwhile, but not an ESSENTIAL skill.  I imagine this one would be quite expensive, such as 5, 10, 15 points.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Fury of Something Something: </span>Another addition to spell casting fury, make it go from the current 14 % chance to crit, add in 3 levels, and make it 16, 18, 20.  Not overpowering, but again, it would add a nice little edge, and another meaningless milestone to achieve.  I'd imagine this could be priced at 4, 8, 12.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
Mastery of XXX:</span> Improvement to Spell Casting Expertise/Mastery of the Past, this could do levels up to 61, 62, 63.  It would be in line with the others in the fact that it wouldn't completely trivial the fizzles on the last expansion, but it would come close, making black steel a never fizzle spell would be nice.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Spell Casting Destruction: </span>This is a skill VERY long overdue imho, the basic idea behind this is that it would add a small BASE amount to spells, must the same way healers get healing adept.  This wouldn't have to add much, even 2, 4, and 6 % would make me happy, hell, 1, 2, and 3 % would make me happy, this skill could be priced accordingly, at 4, 8, and 12.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Bond of the Maelstrom (or some shit): </span>We need an AA damage shield, thats not MUCH more powerful that the current one, but clicks from a skill.  This ideally would be 2 levels, the first would be single target, the second would be group.  Getting rid of another spell slot to a skill is great imo.  There needs to be a small upgrade over the castable DS so people dont bitch about skills being useless, maybe 2 or 3 points higher would be nice, maybe 5 mins more duration.  This skill could cost quite a bit, 5, then 10 maybe.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">The Hero's Call (get it? i just changed the words a bit!):  </span>An instaclick AA coth, useable once every say.... 15? 36? mins, costs no mana, costs no pearl, works EXACLTY like normal coth, so if you're too close you still get agro.  This would be a handy in a few situations, but definately not overpowered.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Hastened Extended Frenzy: </span> I dunno, just do something to make frenzy burnout suck less.  I know it's impossible now to make it NOT suck, so just make it suck less, somehow, i'll pay more points for it to suck less, thats fine.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">More raised Skill Caps:</span>  Yeah, stick em up again, that'd be kinda cool.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">AA to raise resist CAP:  </span>Yes, there is a resist cap, yes it does exist, it's 500, it would be nice for an AA to exist that raised this cap say... 50 per level.  5 levels of the skill, so you can get 750 resists, that would be really nice.  Make it like 3 points a pop.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Pet skills !:  </span>I saw in another thread someone mentioning having AA to give pet all the combat melee skills.  This imo is a BRILLIANT idea, even if they cost the same as the melee skills themselves.  Nothing is more fun that having a pet, except... having a pet that you can upgrade by AA, wonderful idea on this one. Overpowering? not really.  This would fill in another 150ish AA too for the mage and necro class, money in the bank from the design point of view.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Elemental Form: Manifest: </span>Someone else mentioned this in another thread, absolutely wonderful idea as well.  Make the prereq be level 5 in every other skill then charge 20 points for it, I dont give a toss, but having 400hp, 8 mana regen, 35 all saves, and whatever the hell fire form gives, all in one click and slot would be great. (See below for where i got those numbers~)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">New Earth Form: </span>300hp, then 400hp, dunno about cost, but from linear progression it would be 12, and 15, that DOES sound ridiculous though, 9 was ridiculous for level 3 already.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">New Water Form: </span>6 and 8 mana regen.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
New Air Form: </span>30 and 35 all saves.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">
<br />
New Fire Form: </span>Dun care, no one uses it cept maybe in duels... *maybe*, even then earth seems to be the demon of choice.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">New AA Resists and i Guess stats:</span>  Yeah, I love training new AA resists, it's fun.
<br />

<br />
</ul>
<br />

<br />
What do you guys want this expansion? Also, what level cap would you like to see? Level 65, level 70, level 75?  Personally, i'd like to see level 75... sure it would trivialise content, but isn't that the point of expansions... well, more of a biproduct, than an actual purpose, but either way, it's happened EVERY single expansion so far, why should this one be any different? I like the way the game is heading, it's fun.  As for the new levels only working in new zones, heh, wasn't that a rumour with PoP? Wont happen.
<br />

