<br />

<br />
Improvement to Mastery of the Past? Won't happen. Here's why. What happens when you can make spells up to level 63 unfizzlable? Well, you can no longer attempt to use that in mob spell effects for difficulty (a la Luclin). Besides, Mastery of the Past is... for spells that you used to use... in the past. Current spells are damn powerfull and, dispite being well versed in them, still tricky to control. If they weren't this way, they would have been put into your spell book at an earlier level.
