				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">sigh Rhasin I just came up with the idea similar to yours about an ability to share buffs with pet just didn't look at this thread yet <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I would agree with a lot that is said here
<br />

<br />
1.  There should be no more crit AA's imo, its powerful enough.  We have 14% wizards have 21% thats *alot* of crits and while not overpowering for us more crits would expand exponentially for wizards
<br />

<br />
2.  Pet skills, I think it's a good idea but as in my thread Im not confident they could or would implement them decently.  Honestly pets tank pretty well with buffs as is.  Only reason we see them tanking like crap is because they're buffless.  Put an unbuffed warrior against an unslowed PoP mob I bet you he'll last *shorter* than our pets.  So this would have to be carefully moderated if any AA skills were planned for our pets.  I can agree with damage, but tanking is a bit iffy to me considering how often my pet tanks and how well it tanks with only 1 buff
<br />

<br />
3.  Advanced call of the hero, I would only approve of this ability if it allowed coth to be used wher eit would otherwise be restricted due to Sonys random logic.. Since im sick of that logic
<br />

<br />
4. Yes we need someway to upgrade frenzied burnout, its only been almost 2 years now thanks
<br />

<br />
5.  I would buy improved first aid before I buy mastery of the past..  Its the kind of skill that is either completely worthless or insanely overpowered if they raise the cap too far..
<br />

<br />
6.  In general I would rather not have a ton of upgrades to existing abilities since that's boring.  Frenzied burnout, elemental forms are okay since those are luclin but more and more of the same old stuff eh no thanks
<br />

<br />
I think Rhasins idea about Pet bonding so they could get buffs is more or less the best idea i could think of for a new AA.. It would help a ton and would be worth 8 or 9 AA.. I doubt it'll be implemented but we can hope <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Another idea I'll throw out..
<br />

<br />
Activatable "shield" type AA.. Where you would activate it onto your pet and he would take damage similar to the /shield command.. It would last for say 30 seconds or so with a recast of whatever is decided prob 9 mins would be fair<br />_________________<br /><br>
<br />
<img border=0 src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg" />
<br />
